      "rationale": "Experimental operating points (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM through 6000 RPM; 5.0 L/min at 3500 RPM) replicated in CFD with boundary conditions set to measured values ± uncertainty. Blood analog (glycerin-water mixture) viscosity matched to within 2%. Temperature controlled at 37°C ± 1°C."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within ±25% across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements from the FDA generic pump dataset. Agreement within ±18% across all 5 operating points. Worst-case operating condition correctly identified as 2.5 L/min at 6000 RPM in both CFD and experiment. Acceptance criterion met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
