      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, RH, volume-averaged shear stress, exposure time distribution) must be directly traceable to the hemolysis acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH computed from CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time via the power-law hemolysis model. RH is directly used in the regulatory acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs (pressure head, velocity profiles) support model plausibility. All QoIs are relevant to the COU decision."
    },
